author: CNN
description: Family and friends are mourning a National Guard member after an ambush-style shooting in Washington, DC, while another soldier who was also injured near the White House fights for his life. “She’s just passed away,” President Donald Trump said of US Army Spc. Sarah Beckstrom, 20, in a Thanksgiving call to service members. “She’s no longer with us. She’s looking down at us right now.” #CNN #News
title: National Guard shooting suspect faces murder charge after death of one victim

author: CNN
description: The White House is doubling down on its aggressive immigration policies after the shooting of two National Guard members in Washington, DC by an Afghan national suspect. CNN’s senior law enforcement analyst and former FBI Deputy Director Andrew McCabe explores whether President Trump’s threat to “permanently pause migration from all Third World Countries” will make America safer.
title: Will Trump’s threat to ‘pause migration’ make America safer?

author: CNN
description: Surveillance footage shows the moment that an earthquake hit a coffee shop in Anchorage, shaking syrup off the shelves. #alaska #earthquake #cnn
title: 6.0 magnitude earthquake rattles Alaska

author: CNN
description: Every weekday, people go to 26 Federal Plaza in New York to meet with judges handling their immigration cases. But now, federal agents are also roaming the hallways, detaining some men and women without explanation as they exit routine court hearings.
title: ICE detains immigrants as they leave court appointments

author: CNN
description: President Trump posted online that any document signed by former President Biden while he was in office is "hereby terminated, and of no further force or effect." #CNN #News
title: Trump claims he's cancelling anything Biden signed via autopen

author: CNN
description: The US military carried out a follow-up strike on a suspected drug vessel operating in the Caribbean on September 2 after an initial attack did not kill everyone on board, sources familiar with the matter told CNN. That September strike was the first in what became a regular series of attacks on alleged drug boats.  #CNN #News
title: US struck alleged drug boat second time to kill survivors, sources say

author: CNN
description: Hippos regularly wander through neighborhoods at night in the South African town of St. Lucia. This eco-tourism hotspot sits beside one of the country’s largest hippo habitats. #cnn #news #hippos
title: Hippos roam free in South African town

author: CNN
description: The US will reexamine all green cards issued to people from 19 countries “of concern” at President Donald Trump’s direction, as the Trump administration intensifies its immigration crackdown following the shooting of two National Guard members in Washington, DC.  #CNN #News
title: US will reexamine all green cards issued to people from 19 countries ‘of concern’

author: CNN
description:
Andriy Yermak, one of Ukraine’s most influential political operators and a close aide of President Volodymyr Zelensky, resigned hours after anti-corruption agencies raided his home – a major crisis as Kyiv faces new pressure from the US to accept a peace deal to end the war with Russia.

#CNN #News #Ukraine
title: Top Zelensky adviser resigns after anti-corruption raid

author: CNN
description: One of the closest aides of Ukraine’s President Volodymyr Zelensky has resigned on Friday, just hours after the country’s anti-corruption agencies raided his home. Officially the chief of staff to the president, Andriy Yermak has often been seen as Ukraine’s second most powerful man. He has been leading the Ukrainian delegation during recent talks in Geneva with Washington. CNN's Nick Paton Walsh reports.  #CNN #News
title: Zelensky’s top adviser resigns after anti-corruption police raid his home

author: CNN
description: Pope Leo has visited the sunken Basilica of Saint Neophytos in Turkey to take part in celebrations for the 1,700th anniversary of The Council of Nicaea. This ecumenical council produced the Nicene Creed which defined the core Christian doctrines. CNN Vatican Correspondent Christopher Lamb reports. #CNN #news
title: Pope Leo prays at ancient sunken basilica

author: CNN
description: The emotional moment a conservationist found the rare flower that he’d been looking for for years has gone viral. Septi Andriki and a team of conservationists found the rare Rafflesia hasseltii in bloom deep in the rainforest in west Sumatra, Indonesia.
title: 13-year search for rare flower ends in tears of joy

author: CNN
description: Video shows officers lining the streets in Washington, D.C. during the dignified transfer of West Virginia National Guard Member Sarah Beckstrom's remains from MedStar Washington Hospital. #cnn #news #shorts
title: Officers line streets for dignified transfer of National Guard member killed

author: CNN
description: President Donald Trump suggested Thursday that the United States is preparing to take new action against alleged drug trafficking networks in Venezuela, telling service members during a Thanksgiving call that efforts for strikes on land will be starting “very soon.”  #CNN #News
title: Trump: US land action in Venezuela will start ‘very soon’

author: CNN
description: President Donald Trump said on Truth Social that his administration will work to “permanently pause migration from all Third World countries to allow the U.S. system to fully recover.” His comments came after an Afghan national was identified as the suspect in the shooting of two National Guard members in Washington. #CNN #news
title: Trump says US will 'permanently pause migration from all Third World countries'

author: CNN
description: President Donald Trump said his administration will work to “permanently pause migration from all Third World Countries,” though it’s unclear precisely which countries he was referring to. His comments came hours after he announced the death of a National Guard member following a shooting in which the suspect is an Afghan national.  #CNN #News
title: Trump escalates immigration crackdown after National Guard member dies

author: CNN
description: Pope Leo blessed the foundation stone of St Augstine's Church in Pleasant Grove, Dallas, whilst greeting a group of priests in Istanbul. The Pope is making his first trip abroad since his election in May. CNN Vatican Correspondent Christopher Lamb reports. #CNN #news
title: Pope Leo blesses foundation stone of Texas church

author: CNN
description: Born out of the Arab Spring of the 2010s, Tunisia88 is part of an international student-led music movement founded by a Juilliard-trained concert pianist. The program operates in six countries around the world. To hear more positive stories like this, check out the CNN 5 Good Things podcast. New episodes drop every Saturday.
title: Years after the Arab Spring, a Tunisian choir travels thousands of miles to perform #cnn #goodthing

author: CNN
description: The number of people killed in the Hong Kong apartment complex fire has risen to more than 125. Officials have also said as many as 200 people are still missing. CNN's Hanako Montgomery visited the scene and spoke to volunteers helping survivors. #cnn #hongkongfire
title: Hong Kong fire death toll continues to rise
